title: Will Toyota run a Super Bowl ad in 2025?
subtitle: :: Includes, for example, Toyota and Lexus
rules_primary: If Toyota has an ad during the 2025 Football Championship national broadcast after kick-off and before the game ends, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
Clarification 1/26/25 3:00 AM ET: (1) The market called "Budweiser" refers to any advertisement regarding a product of the "Budweiser Family" as defined in Anheuser-Busch 10K filings. This includes but is not limited to Budweiser, Budweiser Select, Bud Light, and Bud Ice. An advertisement for "Cutwater" or "Nutrl" would not satisfy the payout criterion.
Clarification 1/26/25: (2) The market called "Verizon" refers to any advertisement including services they power or provide (if strictly mentioned in the advertisement). This includes but is not limited to an advertisement for "Visible by Verizon" that clearly states/displays "Verizon" in its ad. An advertisement for "Total Wireless" would not satisfy the payout criterion unless the ad clearly states/displays "Verizon" in its ad. 

Additional Clarification 1/26/25: For Budweiser, if any product in the "Budweiser" family is advertised during the game, the market resolves to Yes. That includes Budweiser, Budweiser Select, Bud Light, and Bud Ice. For Pepsi, if any product sold by PepsiCo is advertised during the game, the market resolves to Yes. That includes, for example, Doritos. For Coca-Cola, if any product sold by the Coca-Cola Company is advertised during the game, the market resolves to Yes. That includes, for example, "Fanta" and "Fairlife." For Apple, if any product sold by Apple Inc. is advertised during the game, the market resolves to Yes. That includes, for example, Beats headphones. Additional Clarification 1/28/25 3:00 AM ET: An ad is aired if it is aired as part of a promotional advertisement during a commercial break. An announcer during the game saying, "This is brought to you by <company>" or a viral marketing stunt during the game is not encompassed by the Payout Criterion. The strikes "Toyota" and "Hyundai" encompass any product created by those companies, even if they are not part of the "Toyota" or "Hyundai" brands within those companies. For example, a Lexus ad would resolve the Toyota market to "Yes".

title: Will Elon Musk join the Trump Administration?
expiration_value: On February 5, 2025, press secretary Karoline Leavitt referred to Elon Musk as the leader of DOGE.
rules_primary: If Elon Musk has been nominated or appointed to the Trump Administration (e.g. as a Cabinet Secretary or policy advisor) before May 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: Merely being nominated to a position that requires Senate confirmation (e.g. a federal judgeship or a Cabinet Secretary) is sufficient to resolve as Yes. Clarification 11/14/24 3:00 AM ET: Being a part of a non-governmental organization (which the Department of Government Efficiency, DOGE, may be) is not sufficient to resolve the Contract, even if that organization has some relationship (e.g. is contracted by) with the Trump Administration, if the person in that role is regularly advising the President, or even if that organization receives government financing. However, leading a non-governmental organization *and* holding a Cabinet-level position, or being nominated for one, or holding another position in the White House (e.g. "Senior Policy Advisor") would be sufficient to resolve the Contract.

title: Will Donald Trump be Time Person of the Year in 2024?
subtitle: Donald Trump
rules_primary: If Donald Trump is Time Person of the Year for 2024, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
If there is no Person of the Year (and instead many variations thereof, e.g. Entertainer of the Year, Hero of the Year), that is not encompassed in the Payout Criterion.
If multiple persons win, all persons that are listed are encompassed within the Payout Criterion. If, for example, the Person of the Year is Joe Biden and Kamala Harris, both Joe Biden and Kamala Harris strikes are encompassed within the Payout Criterion. The person must be explicitly named as the Person of the Year or pictured on the/a relevant cover if they are associated with the group/concept winning (the picture is only relevant for a natural human being winning). Some examples to illustrate this:
Jamal Khasogghi would resolve to Yes in 2018, when The Guardians won, as he is also named and shown on a cover and falls within The Guardians. Similarly, Bill Gates would resolve to Yes in 2005. Ashley Judd would resolve to Yes in 2018. If ChatGPT was the Person of the Year, strikes of AI or LLMs would resolve to No, since even if they are conceptually linked, they are not synonymous (and thus are not explicitly named), and are not persons, so it would not matter if they were identified in the image.
Or if Sam Altman was the Person of the Year, and the cover showed a person using ChatGPT on their computer, ChatGPT would not resolve to Yes because it is not a person.
If Time uses language that does not specifically refer to a person or organization (examples being 2018s The Guardians of Truth or 2017s The Silence Breakers), Kalshi will resolve markets to the most simple meaning reasonable. In those cases, Journalists and the Me Too movement would resolve to Yes.

title: Tulsi Gabbard nominated to the Cabinet before Feb 1, 2025?
rules_primary: If Tulsi Gabbard is nominated to the Cabinet before Feb 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: Announcements made by a President-elect will only be effective once they are inaugurated as President. To be clear, if the President appoints (or says he will appoint) the individual to a cabinet-level position, even if that position does not require Senate confirmation, then the market resolves to Yes. For example, the Chief of Staff to the White House is typicallya cabinet-level position that does not require Senate confirmation.

title: Elon Musk nominated to the Cabinet before Feb 1, 2025?
rules_primary: If Elon Musk is nominated to the Cabinet before Feb 1, 2025, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: Announcements made by a President-elect will only be effective once they are inaugurated as President. To be clear, if the President appoints (or says he will appoint) the individual to a cabinet-level position, even if that position does not require Senate confirmation, then the market resolves to Yes. For example, the Chief of Staff to the White House is typicallya cabinet-level position that does not require Senate confirmation. Clarification 11/14/24 3:00 AM ET: Being a part of a non-governmental organization (which the Department of Government Efficiency, DOGE, may be) is not sufficient to resolve the Contract, even if that organization has some relationship (e.g. is contracted by) with the Trump Administration, if the person in that role is regularly advising the President, or even if that organization receives government financing. However, leading a non-governmental organization *and* being nominated to a Cabinet-level position would be sufficient to resolve the Contract.

title: Will Trump win the Electoral College and Trump win the Popular Vote?
yes_sub_title: Trump wins Electoral College, Trump wins Popular Vote
no_sub_title: Trump wins Electoral College, Trump wins Popular Vote
expiration_value: Trump wins Electoral College, Trump wins Popular Vote
rules_primary: If the Republican Party wins the Electoral College and the Republican Party wins the Popular Vote for the U.S. Presidency in  2024, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: The market turns specifically on the party of the person who wins either the Popular Vote or Electoral College. So if the candidates are replaced by members of the same party, the market will still resolve based on whether a member of that party wins the Popular Vote and/or Electoral College.

title: Will the Federal Reserve Hike rates by 0bps at their September 2024 meeting?
subtitle: Hike 0bps
rules_primary: If the Federal Reserve does a Hike of 0bps on September 18, 2024 , then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
This market is mutually exclusive. Therefore, if the Federal Reserve hikes by 50bps, the 50bp market will resolve to Yes and the 25bp market will resolve to No. Only one bucket, at maximum, can resolve to Yes. 

Clarification 10:10 AM ET 8/5/24: If a scheduled FOMC meeting is cancelled and does not occur on its scheduled date, then all strikes in this market resolve to No.

title: When will Bitcoin hit $100k?
subtitle: Before Nov 29th at 7pm ET
rules_primary: If the price of Bitcoin is Above 99999.99 by Nov 29, 2024 at 7:00 PM ET, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: The Contract is settled by taking an average of CF Benchmarks' Bitcoin Real-Time Index (BRTI) in a sixty minute period between 8AM and 7PM, excluding the top 20% and bottom 20% of values. Importantly, only data used between 8AM and 7PM on weekdays are used (save stock market holidays) to resolve the contract.

title: Best AI at year end?
subtitle: Gemini:: Google
rules_primary: If Google has the top-ranked LLM on Dec 31, 2024, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary:
A tie would resolve to No. 

Clarification 3/14/24 6:03 PM ET: The Contract's Underlying states that, "The Underlying for this Contract is the Arena Elo rankings of large language models on the LMSYS Chatbot Arena Leaderboard as checked at 10:00 AM ET daily after Issuance and before <date>." To be clear, this refers to the "rank" column of the leaderboard, not the Arena Elo Score proper. As of this update, the #1 spot is tied between two variations of GPT-4 and Claude 3 Opus. Moreover, the Payout Criterion states that, "If they [the target organization] have an LLM that is tied with another LLM, then the Payout Criterion is not fulfilled." To be clear, if the only tie is with the same organization, that organization's strike would resolve to Yes. So if on the target date the tie is betweentwo variations of GPT-4, then the market would resolve Yes in favor of OpenAI. However, if it is tied between GPT-4 and Claude 3, then both OpenAI and Anthropic's strikes would resolve to No.

title: Will the Fed cut rates 6 times?
subtitle: 6 cuts :: 150bps
rules_primary: If the Fed does exactly 6 cuts of 25 basis points in 2024, the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: To be clear, 25bp of cuts is equal to one cut (so 25bp cut is 1, 50bp cut is 2, 75bp cut is 3, and so on). Note: the original filing had a typographical error that referred to a 25bp cut as an "increase" in the federal funds rate. This has been changed.

title: Will there be a recession by the end of 2024?

title: Will the upper bound of the federal funds rate be above 5.25% following the Fed's June meeting?
subtitle: >5.25% :: 25 bp hike
rules_primary: If the upper bound of the target federal funds rate published on the Federal Reserve's official website is greater than 5.25% following the Federal Reserve's June 14, 2023 meeting, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: This market will expire the first 2:05 PM ET following the release of a Federal Reserve statement for their June 14, 2023 meeting or one week following the last day of that meeting.

title: Will a **recession** start by Q2 2022?
yes_sub_title: At least one negative GDP quarter
no_sub_title: All quarters with at least 0% GDP growth
rules_primary: If the seasonally adjusted annualized percent change in quarterly U.S. real GDP from the previous quarter is strictly less than zero in at least one of Q3 2021, Q4 2021, Q1 2022, and Q2 2022, then the market resolves to Yes.
rules_secondary: Please see RECSS in the Rulebook for more details.
